Ad Text:
We are seeking a Contract Senior Data Architect / Data Modeller to lead the design of a common enterprise data model supporting the migration of fragmented data assets from SAS NEO to a Databricks Lakehouse platform.

This role plays a critical part in establishing a unified, governed data foundation that standardises core entities, definitions, and relationships across the organisation, enabling scalable analytics, reporting, and AI/ML use cases.

You will work across architecture, data engineering, analytics, and business teams to rationalise existing schemas, translate embedded business logic, and define canonical domains aligned to modern Lakehouse and cloud data architecture principles.

Key Responsibilities
Design conceptual, logical, and physical data models supporting enterprise analytics and AI
Define canonical data domains, entities, and relationships
Map legacy SAS NEO datasets and unstructured sources to target Databricks models
Translate embedded business logic into governed, reusable data structures
Define OLTP, OLAP, and dimensional models (star/snowflake)
Establish metadata, lineage, and documentation standards
Ensure alignment with Lakehouse, ELT, and cloud architecture patterns
Collaborate with engineers, architects, and stakeholders on target-state design
Required Skills & Experience
Strong experience in Data Architecture, Data Modelling & Design
Proven migration experience to Databricks or Lakehouse platforms
Conceptual, logical and physical modelling expertise
Dimensional modelling (star/snowflake) and OLTP vs OLAP design
Advanced SQL
Experience with relational databases (SQL Server, Oracle, Postgres, MySQL, SAS)
Cloud platforms: Azure, AWS or GCP
Data integration & ETL/ELT design patterns
Metadata management, lineage, and governance frameworks
Nice to Have
Python, Scala, or Spark
Informatica, ADF, Talend, Boomi, SSIS
Kafka / Event Hubs / streaming
Power BI, Tableau, Qlik
MDM and data quality tooling
Infrastructure-as-code exposure (Terraform / ARM)
If you would like to hear more please APPLY below. Australian Citizens or PR only.

We’re looking for a highly analytical, data-driven marketer who gets excited by digging into raw data, uncovering patterns, and turning insight into action. Someone who thrives on understanding customer journeys end-to-end and using data to fuel smarter lead generation, automation and campaign performance.

 

About the role



As the Marketing Insights & Lead Generation Manager, you will play a critical role in building and scaling an elite, data-led lead generation engine for Vocus.




This role is about deep analysis, insight generation and optimisation. You will work hand-in-glove with our Marketing Automation & CRM Manager, using data to inform how leads are sourced, segmented, nurtured, scored and converted across the funnel.




You’ll be responsible for analysing various data sets (CRM, campaign, behavioural, customer and third-party data), identifying opportunities, and translating insight into clear actions that improve demand generation, campaign effectiveness and customer experience.

 

What you’ll be responsible for



Lead Generation & Demand Optimisation

Analyse lead, opportunity and campaign data to identify performance drivers, gaps and optimisation opportunities across the full funnel
Support the design and ongoing refinement of lead nurture programs, working closely with the Marketing Automation & CRM Manager
Use insights to inform targeting, segmentation, messaging, CTAs and offers to improve conversion and pipeline contribution

 

Customer & Market Insights

Deeply analyse customer behaviour, preferences and buying signals across Simple Enterprise, Mid-Market and SMB segments
Identify trends, patterns and opportunities from raw data sets and translate them into actionable insights
Analyse competitive offers and market activity to inform positioning, propositions and campaign strategy

 

Customer Journey Analysis

Map and continuously refine customer journeys using data to understand drop-off points, friction and moments of opportunity
Cross-match behavioural, campaign and CRM data to uncover how customers move through the funnel and lifecycle
Identify opportunities for personalisation, automation and smarter engagement at each stage

 

Data Analysis & Reporting

Own the analysis and interpretation of marketing and sales data, turning complex data into clear, compelling insights
Build and maintain dashboards, reports and ad-hoc analysis to support decision-making (monthly MBRs and on-demand reporting)
Track and report on key KPIs including lead quality, conversion rates, pipeline contribution, campaign ROI and customer engagement

 

CRM & Data Management (Salesforce)

Support end-to-end lead and data management within Salesforce, including data enrichment, list processing and lead reporting
Partner closely with CRM, SFMC and data teams to ensure data integrity, usability and insight generation
Support opportunity campaign creation for outbound sales and coordination of EDM and communication lists

 

Collaboration & Stakeholder Engagement

Work closely with the Marketing Automation & CRM Manager to operationalise insights into automated journeys and campaigns
Partner with sales, digital performance, segment leads and data teams to align insight, execution and outcomes
Communicate insights clearly to stakeholders, helping teams understand the “so what” and “what next”

 

What you’ll bring to the role



Experience & Background

8–10+ years’ experience in B2B marketing, insights, demand generation or analytics-focused roles
Experience in telecommunications, technology, SaaS or digital infrastructure highly regarded
Degree in Marketing, Business, Analytics, Data, or equivalent industry experience (MBA or analytics qualifications highly regarded)

 

Capabilities & Skills

Strong data and analytical capability - confident working with large, complex data sets
Advanced Excel skills (pivot tables, formulas, data manipulation) and strong reporting capability
Experience working with CRM and marketing automation platforms (Salesforce / SFMC experience highly regarded)
Deep understanding of lead generation mechanics, funnels, lifecycle marketing and customer journeys
Commercially minded with the ability to translate data into clear, actionable recommendations
Comfortable operating in fast-paced, evolving environments with ambiguity

The Senior Manager, Statistical Programming is responsible for planning and executing or overseeing projects by coordinating staff and processes to deliver projects on time, within budget and with the desired outcomes while ensuring the trial is conducted in accordance with the protocol, company Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), ICH GCP guidelines and other applicable regulatory requirements.

Core Responsibilities
• Provide technical leadership and oversight for statistical programming deliverables, ensuring high-quality, compliant datasets, tables, listings, and figures through effective cross-functional collaboration and adherence to CDISC standards, regulatory requirements, and internal SOPs.
• Analyse study protocols, statistical analysis plans, and sponsor requirements to translate business and research needs into technical programming specifications.
• Develop, modify, and validate SAS programs to generate clinical datasets, tables, listings, and figures (TLFs) in accordance with CDISC SDTM and ADaM standards.
• Perform unit testing, debugging, validation, and documentation of statistical programs to ensure data integrity and reproducibility.
• Maintain and enhance existing programming codebases, implementing improvements to efficiency, reliability, and standardisation.
• Collaborate with Biostatistics, Data Management, PK, Clinical Operations, and Medical Writing teams to ensure technical consistency, accurate data flow, and timely delivery of programming outputs.
• Identify, analyse, and resolve programming defects, performance issues, and data inconsistencies throughout the project lifecycle.
• Ensure all programming activities comply with internal SOPs, regulatory requirements, and applicable quality standards.
• Contribute to the development, maintenance, and optimisation of programming macros, utilities, libraries, and tools to support scalable and reusable solutions.
• Participate in peer code reviews and quality checks to ensure adherence to technical standards and best practices.
• Support audit and inspection activities by providing technical explanations, programming documentation, and validated outputs as required.
• Provide technical guidance and knowledge sharing to colleagues on programming methodologies, standards, and tools, as needed.
• Perform other programming-related duties as directed by the Line Manager.


Departmental Responsibilities
• Collaborate effectively with members of the Biometrics department to support integrated technical delivery of clinical data outputs.
• Identify and mitigate technical risks related to statistical programming deliverables.
• Participate in technical training and continuous professional development related to programming tools, standards, and methodologies.
• Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives relating to programming processes, standards, and automation.
• Manage sponsor communication, project timelines, risks, and programming-related resources, including forecasting, change control, and issue resolution, to ensure successful and timely project delivery.


Qualifications, Skills and Experience
• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Software Engineering, or a related quantitative discipline.
• Minimum 5 years of hands-on programming experience, with the majority of time spent writing, testing, and maintaining code.
• Demonstrated expertise in SAS programming, including development of SDTM and ADaM datasets.
• Strong experience in application-style programming logic, data processing workflows, and system optimisation.
• Proven ability to analyse requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
• Experience working within regulated environments and adhering to documented standards and procedures.
• Strong problem-solving, debugging, and analytical skills.

Stimulating work
Project diversity
An intellectual challenge
An agile & flexible workplace
Opportunity to progress
Stability
Sense of community
A leadership team that are working together on a common goal
Flexible work options
Great tools / tech to do your job

Ad Text:
About Us

Join us at Cleanaway and contribute to making a sustainable future possible, together.

We transform waste into resources and renewable energy.  When you start to think of waste as a resource, it opens a world of possibilities.

As a high growth, ASX listed organisation with over 10,000 employees, our goal is to be recognised by our customers as the most innovative and sustainable waste management company with industry leading HSE performance.  We are Australia’s largest company in this sector, providing essential services to millions of customers and communities nationally.

The Opportunity

We are seeking a highly capable and commercially minded Senior FP&A Analyst to join Cleanaway’s Group Finance team on a 6-month fixed-term contract. 

Sitting within the Group FP&A function, this role plays an integral part in delivering Cleanaway’s financial planning and reporting processes, including forecast and monthly reporting. You’ll be responsible for preparing analysis, interpreting financial performance, and providing insights that support decision-making across Group and Corporate stakeholders. Further, you’ll be leading the KPI and Value Driver reporting process, including governance on metrics and reporting. 

This is a hands-on role that would suit an experienced analyst who enjoys the structure of ASX and BAU cycles, has excellent attention to detail, and is confident working with financial systems and large data sets. You will work closely with other analysts, Corporate Finance, and business partners across the Strategic Business Units (SBUs). 

 

Key Responsibilities 

Support the forecasting and budgeting process, working with finance business partners to consolidate, review, and validate inputs. 
Supporting and developing our Key Performance Indicators and Value Drivers across our segments, including the reporting and governance framework. 
Prepare and deliver accurate and timely monthly performance reporting, including actuals vs budget/forecast analysis for both Group, Segment and Corporate Functions. 
Assist with preparation of reporting packs and presentations for Monthly Operating Reviews (MORs) and internal executive stakeholders. 
Work with Corporate Functions to track and report overhead performance, highlighting key drivers and variances. 
Driving the preparation of board reporting, including Board Insight Papers, along with ASX-related external reporting requirements. 
Collaborating with each Strategic Business Units (SBU) to support and align on performance and analysis requirements. 
Use tools such as TM1 (PAW/PAFE) and Power BI to extract, analyse and present data in a clear and meaningful way. 
Assist in the development and maintenance of financial models, templates, and standardised reports. 
Collaborate with the wider Group FP&A team and SBUs to ensure alignment and clarity across financial deliverables and deadlines. 

About You

You bring strong commercial acumen, advanced analytical capability, and the confidence to influence senior stakeholders in a complex organisation.

 

8+ years of experience in Financial Planning & Analysis, management reporting, or similar commercial finance roles. 
Proven experience supporting BAU financial cycles including budgeting, forecasting, and month-end reporting. 
Strong analytical skills with attention to detail, and ability to interpret financial data into clear insights. 
Proficiency in financial systems such as TM1 (PAW/PAFE), Power BI, and advanced Excel. 
Experience working in a large, complex, or matrixed organisation – ASX-listed or similar preferred. 
Strong financial acumen, with an understanding of forecasting methodologies and value drivers. 
Strong interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to work effectively with finance and non-finance stakeholders. 

Why join Cleanaway? 

Competitive salary package
Flexible working arrangements
Career opportunities in a high growth, Australian business
Supportive and safe work environment
Paid parental leave
Great company benefits: Employee share program, company discounts, salary packaging, flu vaccinations, EAP, discounts on private health insurance and more.

Our Process

Our recruitment process involves a number of checks including, but not limited to, criminal history, medicals, drug & alcohol testing, as well as verification of qualifications, licences and right-to-work status.

We are dedicated to improving employment outcomes and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. We also welcome candidates of all ages, abilities, gender identities, experiences (including veterans), and cultural backgrounds.

If you require any adjustments during the recruitment process, please contact us by emailing inclusion@cleanaway.com.au.

Join us on our exciting journey towards a sustainable future.

Simply click the Apply button or visit https://www.cleanaway.com.au/about-us/careers and let's make a positive impact together.

About the Role/Team

Finance at Canva is on an exciting journey—scaling the foundations that support a rapidly growing global company, while making our processes smarter, simpler, and more empowering for our teams. The Finance Transformation team sits at the heart of this mission.

We're looking for a Finance Transformation Senior Manager who’s passionate about solving complex problems, improving processes end-to-end, and helping teams work more efficiently through technology, automation, and AI-enabled solutions. You’ll work cross-functionally across Finance, along with Finance Systems, Finance Data and the broader business, helping shape and execute Canva’s finance transformation projects — with a focus on process reengineering, driving simplification, automation and AI-driven solutions. You’ll help share the future of how Finance works at Canva.

If you love digging into business processes, running cross-functional projects, driving change, and finding opportunities to streamline and simplify — this role is made for you.

What you’ll do (responsibilities)

Lead Finance Process Transformation: Identify, design, and deliver scalable improvements across key global finance processes (Revenue, Billing, Payables, Reporting, etc.), balancing innovation with strong control and compliance. Help embed AI-enabled ways of working, drive adoption and education, help teams identify problems and expected outcomes - focusing on efficiency, accuracy, repeatability, and standardisation.
Project, Program and Change Management: Lead transformation programs of varying scale, ensuring cross-functional stakeholder alignment, governance, and smooth change adoption across teams. Coordinate project activities, dependencies, and timelines to ensure alignment between teams.Help unblock, remove ambiguity, and support smooth project execution.
Drive Technology Enablement: Partner with Finance Systems, Data, and Engineering teams to implement automation, system integrations, and AI-based solutions that streamline end-to-end workflows.
Help shape the Transformation Roadmap: Collaborating with finance and business leaders to define the strategic direction for the Finance Technology stack and transformation priorities.
Data, Insight & Automation: Champion data-driven decision-making - ensuring finance data is leveraged effectively for reporting, analytics, and automation.

What we're looking for

Significant experience in Finance Transformation, or Process Improvement roles (experience in fast-scaling tech, SaaS, or global environments strongly preferred).
A background in Finance with a Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, or a related field is a big plus.
Experience with driving process redesign. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, able to break down ambiguity into actionable steps.
Familiarity with finance ERP, billing and reporting systems (e.g., Workday, Netsuite, Zuora, Salesforce, Anaplan) and an understanding of data and automation and AI platforms.
Proven ability to lead large scale transformation programs end-to-end from strategy and design to implementation and embedding.
A balance of big-picture vision and detail orientation, with a strong understanding of finance processes and data flows.
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills; able to work cross-functionally without effort, translating between finance, technical and business teams.
Growth mindset. Passion for continuous improvement and leveraging new technologies (AI, automation, analytics) to elevate finance impact and scale finance operations.

We'd love it if you have:

Familiarity with Agile, Lean, or continuous improvement approaches.

We’re a small new team that is just getting started, so you aren’t afraid to roll up your sleeves, get into the detail. Able to determine and play whatever role is needed to make projects a success: analyst, project coordinator, facilitator, tester, or change champion.

Why You’ll Love It Here

You’ll shape the future of how finance operates at one of the world’s most loved design platforms.

You’ll work with world-class teams across Finance, IT, Data and the business in an environment that encourages experimentation and learning.

You’ll have autonomy and ownership to lead high-impact transformation initiatives that directly influence Canva’s scalability and success.

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too
Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers
An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more
Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other stuff to know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!

Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

Job Title: Senior Technical Business Analyst - AI projects
Ad Text:
Future Secure AI (FSAI) is a fast‑growing enterprise AI company built in deep partnership with one of the world’s largest financial institutions. We work directly with C‑suite leaders across global enterprises to deliver AI solutions that transform how organisations operate.

We’re expanding rapidly and are now looking for a Senior Technical Business Analyst to join our Sydney team and help shape several high‑impact AI initiatives already underway.

Why join us

·       Work on real enterprise AI projects with global reach

·       Collaborate with senior leaders and world‑class technical teams

·       Hybrid work environment based in Sydney CBD

·       Opportunity to influence product direction and delivery

·       Exposure to cutting‑edge AI use cases across multiple industries

The Role

As our Senior Technical Business Analyst, you’ll lead analysis and delivery across a portfolio of complex AI and technology projects. You’ll work closely with product, engineering, and enterprise stakeholders to translate strategy into clear requirements and ensure successful execution.

You will:

·       Facilitate workshops, gather requirements, and define user stories for large‑scale enterprise initiatives

·       Analyse data, processes, and workflows to support decision‑making and risk management

·       Partner with senior leaders to shape delivery strategies and prioritise initiatives

·       Support agile teams by clarifying requirements, removing blockers, and enabling fast decision‑making

·       Build a deep understanding of our AI products and contribute to continuous improvement

·       Work across multiple use cases, including emerging AI capabilities and new product features

About You

·       You’re a confident, proactive Senior BA who thrives in complex environments and enjoys working at the intersection of business, technology, and innovation.

You bring:

·       8+ years as a Business Analyst, ideally in enterprise or consulting environments

·       Strong experience leading complex technology or AI‑related projects

·       Excellent facilitation skills and experience running inception and requirements workshops

·       Solid understanding of software development processes, compliance, and regulatory considerations

·       Ability to work in fast‑paced, agile environments

·       Strong communication skills and the ability to influence stakeholders at all levels

·       Proficiency with Jira, Confluence, and modern BA tools

·       Exposure to AI or machine learning projects (preferred but not essential)

What success looks like

·       You quickly build trust with senior stakeholders

·       You bring clarity to complex problems and drive outcomes

·       You help shape the direction of new AI initiatives

·       You contribute to a culture of high performance and collaboration

Ready to make an impact?

If you’re excited about working with cutting‑edge AI, partnering with global leaders, and joining a high‑growth company, we’d love to hear from you.

For a quicker response, we encourage you to apply directly through our website at https://www.futuresecure.ai/. There, you can meet our Digital Co-worker and experience our product first hand.

Hybrid working, supportive culture, WFH flexibility
$140-160K + super + bonus on offer
Requires strong excel, modelling and presentation capabilities
Reporting into the Group FP&A Manager of this ASX200, this Senior Analyst role presents a compelling opportunity to join an Australian institution.

You'll play a crucial role in the delivery of budgeting, forecasting, strategic planning, board reporting and consolidated management reporting for the group.

You'll partner with a variety of senior stakeholders across the Corporate entity, in the delivery of insights and decision support, as well as ad hoc analysis and reporting when required. Whilst you'll also be involved in ongoing continuous improvement projects.

You are CA or CPA qualified, with a background working as an Analyst or Senior Analyst, within a group-level F&A function of a complex, ASX-listed Blue Chip corporate.

You'll have advanced Excel skills, financial modelling capability and proven business partnering capability. You'll also be ambitious and looking to move towards a leadership role in future.
